{
  "stem": "1282.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We're coming.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's just signing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] now?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my name is William Basch.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was born in a small village in the Carpathian Mountains.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I was born, it was Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was the most eastern side, eastern tip of Czechoslovakia, small, Ruthenian village.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time it was called Sasovo.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It has changed since then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That territory belonged to Hungary-Austria prior to 1914.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1914, when Czechoslovakia was created, it was created out of three territories, Bohemia, Slovakia, and Carpathia.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So 1918 to 1938, it became Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In 1938, because the Hungarians had an allied agreement sort of alliance with Hitler, he allowed them to rip Czechoslovakia part and has given back that territory to the Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So in 1938, it became under the supervision of the Hungarian government.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, what they did, the Russians, they annexed the territory.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Instead of being just an occupied satellite, they annexed it to the Ukraine because that gave them an access, a direct route from Moscow through the Ukraine to Germany without crossing any other.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Territorial-wise, they needed that area.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So  it's annexed to the Ukraine, and it has never been returned, neither to Hungary, neither to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It is part of the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1927.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "June 4.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1927.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Basically two.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were-- we referred to them as the Ruthenians, or Russian peasantry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a farming village.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the population was mostly Greek Orthodox-- oddly, but that's how it was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were Greek Orthodox, approximately 3,000 Gentile people and approximately 35 to 40 Jewish families living in that village.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the whole village, about 3,000-plus.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In our home, of course, I had my father, mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then I had an older brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Arthur, my oldest brother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after-- my father's name was Martin, Martin Basch.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
